summary: This is an FBI evidence collection log documenting the seizure of Epstein-related case materials from the Palm Beach Police Department on October 8, 2021. The items collected include two bankers boxes containing various case materials, along with physical media such as CDs, VHS tapes, and cassette tapes.

locations: Town of Palm Beach's storage warehouse
keyFacts: On October 8, 2021, the FBI collected Epstein-related evidence from the Palm Beach Police Department, indicating ongoing investigation activities years after Epstein's death.
The evidence included two bankers boxes of case materials plus various physical media: 4 CDs, 1 VHS tape, 2 cassette tapes, and 4 micro cassette tapes.
The evidence was recovered from inside the Town of Palm Beach's storage warehouse, suggesting long-term storage of case materials.
The FBI case ID is 50D-NY-3027571, related to Jeffrey Epstein and child sex trafficking allegations.
The document shows coordination between federal (FBI) and local (Palm Beach Police Department) law enforcement agencies in the Epstein investigation.
